##She turned her head for a moment, thinking it was her father

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

Since the city was shut down, 217 medical teams have been sent from all over the country, with a total of 25,633 people to support Hubei. Among the countless front-line workers, the medical personnel sent to Hubei from other places are a part that can be counted. More people on the front lines are hiding behind numbers too big to count. Among them, there is a group that can not be ignored: the front line workers who have become parents.
As parents, their greatest fear may not be their own safety, but the children behind them.
A community worker in Wuhan, she counts, reports and calls ambulances as people fall ill, as well as community purchases and donations, in the face of an epidemic that has never been more complex. She has two children, the first in primary school, the second is less than a year old, in order to be able to concentrate on community work, she was cruel, to the second weaned. Fearing cross-contamination, she began using communal chopsticks at home, even when sharing a room and avoiding each other.
A nurse from Guangxi who supports Wuhan is also a mother of two. Before parting, the children held her and cried. Mother coax them, there is a virus outside, very strong, will make people sick, mother to fight the virus, the virus to run back. During her break at the front, she used a watercolor pen to draw pictures of children in protective clothing, holding a large syringe in one hand and aiming it at the drooping eyebrows of coronavirus clutched in the other. For the brother and sister, it's proof that mom fought the monster.
She found it hard to understand what was going on in the outside world. The children will not yet understand why close parents must leave home. But one day they will. The parents took place in the turn of the winter and spring of the story, and when all is over, then slowly tell them to listen.

Editor, sugar maple

It's like having your mom around

On January 26, the first aid medical team from Tianjin set out for Wuhan. The team consisted of 138 people. Nurse Xing Rui was one of them. On that day, she told her daughter that her mother was going to Wuhan. Seven and a half year old SCISCI cried on the spot.

In fact, she was used to her mother not being with her every day like other mothers. Many weekends during the day, she did her homework alone at home, while her mother slept in her room, preparing for the night shift, or just after the night shift. Once in a while, when a mother picks up her daughter from school, Scisci gets excited and says, "there's a difference in the look and the expression. "

But this time, SCISCI felt her mother would be "hard to come back to, " as if she had never been apart for so long, and for how long was anyone's guess.

SCISCI was doing her winter homework, and there was a word in her Chinese exercise that she didn't recognize, "jeopardy. " . She asked her mother what it meant, and she said, danger is danger, disaster is disaster, "Wuhan people are in this situation right now. "SCISCI thought his mother would leave to cry, finished crying, Xingrui began to carry out responsibility education. I say it's our duty. It's our job. I have a lot of students over there, too. Security will be fine. You have to trust me. "

SCISCI went to the airport to see her off to war, and on that day, an instant was captured by a CCTV reporter on her knees -- lower than she was -- holding her daughter's hand, both of them wearing masks. Later, that photo on the big screen of the Lantern Festival party, several friends and colleagues took down to send Xing Rui see. She was pleased, but also know, "in Hubei Support of the tens of thousands of medical staff, some people may have two children at home, some children may be even smaller than my children, they actually miss their children more. ". "

Xing Rui did not know how long the battle would last. On the phone, Scisci told Xing to wear her mother's t shirt to bed every night and hold her mother's pillow. A familiar smell can help a child settle down quickly, just as a mother can.

On her 26th day in Wuhan, Scisci wrote her a letter. There was a picture of the three of them together, with candy, hearts, and a rainbow. Dear Mom, today is February 20,2020, the 26th day since mom left home. Mom, I thought you said you'd be back after I finished the milk. I've been drinking it for days. Why aren't you back yet? I can't wait to see you. "At the end of the line was a small round face with the corner of its mouth turned down as it wept.

The sadness of this separation is shared by all on the front lines. No one wants to leave their family or their children, but in the moment of choice, they instinctively take the other side.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A letter from SCISCI to his mother

The empathy of parents binds them together

More than 1,000 kilometers away, Luo Ronggang, a Baidu engineer in Shanghai, is working from home. This period of isolation at home was a rare time for him to spend with his family.

Luo Ronggang is mainly responsible for the research and development of Small Smart Speaker for children. He is also the father of two daughters, the eldest in kindergarten and the youngest just one year old. As a parent, the perspective is always a child's perspective, giving the world a soft filter. As a result, some of the features that Jingluo Ronggang has studied and developed seem to have their own "old father" aura.

Reading to girls is a habit of Luo Ronggang. But sometimes he comes home from work in the wee hours. Daughters are beginning to understand what "work" and "overtime" mean. Luo often feels guilty about it, though he often makes up for it by buying snacks, picture books and toys for his children after working overtime.

Last October, his small smart speakers team hatched an idea to put voice customization into small smart speakers and read stories to children in the voices of their families. Many on the team have become parents, sharing the experience of not being able to sleep with their children because of overtime.

The project will begin shortly. This is a large-scale cross-regional, cross-sectoral cooperation, the goal is to 2020 before the Lunar New Year, the actual development time is less than a month.

The difficulty of development exists in many aspects. Technically, they found the GPU cost and the server pressure to train the parents'voice to be very high. After discussion, they settled on a more eclectic approach: Parents Record 20 sentences, and then create the model offline when the server is idle. Users can wait up to an hour to generate sentences with their own tone and intonation.

In the first experiment, no one knew how the training would turn out. They trained the first prototype using the voice of the most senior T10 engineer on the project. The results were surprising. The senior engineer's voice was already highly recognisable, and when it came out, it was instantly recognisable to both the people gathered in the office and those working remotely.

It was the last test before it went live, and the team spent a week in Beijing shutting down. Everyone worked intensively in an underground conference room, working late and sometimes until two in the morning. During that week, Luo ronggang would video chat with his family every morning after seven. It was the most relaxing time of the day, even more relaxing than sleeping. Because going back to the hotel to sleep is just "a temporary sleep. ".

Soon after the one-week closure period ended, the new function went online, and soon after that, the city of Wuhan was closed. Smart speakers are not on the front lines of the fight against the epidemic, but many are parents. In the jumble of News, there was one category that caught their attention: front-line workers who were parents.

Doctors, nurses, police officers and volunteers, they noted, were most concerned not about their own safety but about not being able to see their young children. There was once a news story about a woman doctor from Hubei. Before she left, the child cried for an hour with her mother, but her mother said, "you don't want your mother to go, but your mother must go, too, the mother goes is in order to let more children's father and mother may safely accompany their baby at home. "

The empathy of parents binds them together. Beginning on January 30, small degree together with degree Xiaoman finance to fight in Wuhan Front Line to participate in epidemic prevention and rescue work of medical staff family donated 20,000 small degree smart screen at home. The video calling function, the epidemic report function, as well as Luo Ronggang's team on-line voice customization function, has become the connection these can not go home the medical staff and the family a free door.

Luo Ronggang's daughter plays with a small smart screen

For a very special time

On the third day of her arrival in Wuhan, Xing Rui read in a push about the donation of 20,000 smart screens at home to the front-line staff. She filled out the application information, and soon, the information was approved, and the family in Tianjin received a small degree smart screen at home.

With the new toy, SCISCI's attention was partly diverted and his thoughts redirected.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
SCISCI is playing with a tiny smart screen

SCISCI reads from an English picture book at home, and when she's done, she sends the Audio to her mother. She sometimes performs her talent by video phone, and her latest act is singing and dancing "Red Sarirang, " after which she runs to the piano to play a few lines. Xing Rui would talk to Scisci through the screen, telling him interesting things about her. Such as the hotel entrance of the dog, the wind sprout trees, such as the canteen to help cook volunteers, as well as their own down from the radish made of pickles.

SCISCI became unusually concerned about her mother's well being. She has to ask every day, small degrees, what is the temperature in Wuhan today? And then we'll talk to mom. When the temperature dropped from 15c to 5C, SCISCI reminded her to wear more clothes to keep the baby warm. Xing Rui described that day as "like the late autumn in the north, but it was the early spring in Wuhan. ". " She photographed the leaves that had been beaten down by the spring rain. "when the dead leaves fall, new shoots must grow. Will the warm spring flowers be far behind? "

Imitating the Real Voice of mom and dad is a form of accompanying relatives at Special Times. But beyond that, physical companionship can never be replaced. Now, Luo Ronggang works from home. Every day at noon, her daughter to nap, hidden in a small smart screen "Dad" read a story to her. In the evenings, Luo would try to put his work aside and go to his daughters'bedside to read them a story.

Back before the Spring Festival, before the outbreak, Luo Ronggang and everyone on the small smart speaker team did not realize that they might be doing a powerful thing. That day, Luo Rong just came home from the outside, he prepares to test the new line voice to order function on the body of little daughter. He recorded a speech, which generated a custom-made story recited in his own voice, and then remotely controlled his own speaker, where he hid behind a door and watched his young daughter's reactions. The girl was sitting with her back to the speaker. When the automatic "Dad" sound came from behind her, she turned her head and thought it was him coming back.
